In this case the `SKIPNA` value will be checked for every iteration of the loop until the valid element is found. Compiler will probably optimize the code and remove `|| 0` for `SKIPNA == 0`. 

Anyways, It is more efficient and clear to have two separate paths: one for `SKIPNA == 0` and another for `SKIPNA == 1`. So once you test your `pos` to be inside the group bounds, then you do
```
if (SKIPNA) {

// Your loop to find the first non-missing element

} else {

// Simply return the nth element no matter if it is valid or not

}
```

